<br>
The problem, as I see it, is that a large part of the game has turned into a race.  A mob that everyone wants is up, and it's a sprint to see who can get there first in sufficient force.  Either that, or it's an interminable camp (a la Lodi), with everyone calling everyone else a KSer.  <br>
<br>
So take the race/camp aspect out of it.  Make a few/some/all of the heavily contested mobs non-aggro and non-targettable until they are handed a particular item or key.  Then, make that &quot;key&quot; no drop, no rent, and lore.  You could have the key randomly dropped off mobs in that zone, or have it dropped randomly off mobs across many zones (kind of the way words and runes and the such drop).  <br>
<br>
Whether this works would depend, at least in part, on how often the mobs spawns and how frequently the necessary key drops.  If four different guilds each have the &quot;King Tormax key&quot; on a dozen different characters and are just waiting for King Tormax to spawn, it's really not going to improve matters very much.  Of course, they'd have to keep their toons up 24/7 to avoid losing a no drop, no rent key, but that's doable.  <br>
<br>
I'm sure there are objections to this idea, and I'm sure it could be improved, but the current system of race/camp can be quite frustrating. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eudamanslayer>EudaManslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 1236<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(4/30/03 8:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3228.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Contested Mobs</span><hr size=1> Genious... so just have people with trade up trying to hand in an item when they dont have the people there to then drag the mob around as per normal... Not to mention thats something you'd have to FIND a programer at SoE, fucking NAIL thier feet infront of the computer and say &quot;WORK BITCH.&quot;<br>
