I don't understand why the Lodizal situation is any different than any other mob.  More than likely it comes from being a gimp mob with so-so loot on a standard timer in a zone with little to no danger.  But you still have to be able to kill the bastard, so what's the argument?<br>
<br>
Personally, I look at it this way.  If you're KS'd while in a BATTLE and attempting to KILL THE MOB, then you've got every right in the world to be upset.  If you're level 60+ and you're kiting Lodi around in an ATTEMPT TO KILL HIM, then the same rule applies.<br>
<br>
However, I've got no sympathy at all for the lower-level person who thinks that, because they got aggro, they can run him around the zone for half an hour while their buddies get there to help with the kill.  Stalling techniques are not the same as being engaged in battle, and if someone else wanders in who wants to engage the mob in a legitamate fight, then you lose.<br>
<br>
If you get there and find the mob up, you either kill it or leave it alone.  If you're camping the spawn point and it pops, you either kill it of leave it alone.  Just like it is with every other mob in the game.<br>
<br>
